==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
Of Hebrew origin (the tenth letter of the Hebrew alphabet)

===Pronunciation===
ἰῶτα / iōta / ee-o'-tah

===Noun===
'''ἰῶτα'''

# “iota”, the name of the eighth letter of the Greek alphabet, put (figuratively) for a very small part of anything: - [[jot]].

